const faqs = [
  { q: "How much is my Peoria business worth?", a: "Most Main Street businesses in Peoria are valued on a multiple of seller's discretionary earnings, adjusted for your lease, your books, and how dependent the business is on you. As a Certified Business Intermediary, Phil builds a real valuation from your numbers and from what comparable West Valley businesses have actually sold for. Start with a free, confidential valuation and you will know where you stand." },
  { q: "Does spring training affect what my P83-area restaurant or bar is worth?", a: "It can. The Mariners and Padres draw large crowds to the Peoria Sports Complex every February and March, which lifts revenue for nearby restaurants and bars. Buyers know this, so a smart broker shows them the full-year picture and explains the seasonality rather than letting it raise questions during due diligence." },
  { q: "I own a medical or dental practice in North Peoria. Is selling a practice different?", a: "Yes. Healthcare is Peoria's largest sector, and practice sales have their own buyer pool, their own valuation approach, and licensing and credentialing steps a retail sale never touches. Phil has the experience to package a practice the way qualified buyers and their lenders expect to see it." },
  { q: "Who buys businesses in Peoria, and where do buyers come from?", a: "Buyers come from across the West Valley, including Glendale, Surprise, and Sun City, plus a steady stream of people relocating to the area for the growth along Loop 303. Phil markets to a vetted pool of local and out-of-state buyers, which is how you create competition for your business." },
